  "texts": [
    "(2.22)We have been explicit here with how the normal ordering is taken in the βγ 2 term.",
    "Note that zeroes of ξ + are necessarily zeroes of β.",
    "In a correlation function, we can associate γ ∼ -ξ -/ξ + in the patch where ξ + ̸ = 0.",
    "As such, we see that β has zeroes and γ has poles at the removed points.A comment on background charges.",
    "In order to interpret ξ -/ξ + as a projective coordinate, we must work in a patch in which ξ + ̸ = 0."
